.SH NAME
RTCSctpTransport.maxMessageSize \- RTCSctpTransport: maxMessageSize
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]maxMessageSize\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]RTCSctpTransport\f[R] interface indicates the maximum size of a
message that can be sent using the \f[CR]RTCDataChannel.send()\f[R]
method.
.SH VALUE
An integer value giving the maximum size, in bytes, of a message which
can be sent using the \f[CR]RTCDataChannel.send()\f[R] method.
.SH EXAMPLES
This example shows how you might split up a string into small enough
parts to send based on maximum message size.
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// Function splits strings to a specified size and returns array.\f[R]
\f[B]function\f[R] splitStringToMax(str, maxLength) {
  \f[B]const\f[R] result = [];
  \f[B]let\f[R] i = 0;
  \f[B]while\f[R] (i < str.length) {
    result.push(str.substring(i, i + maxLength));
    i += maxLength;
  }
  \f[B]return\f[R] result;
}

\f[B]const\f[R] peerConnection = \f[B]new\f[R] RTCPeerConnection(options);
\f[B]const\f[R] channel = peerConnection.createDataChannel(\(dqchat\(dq);
channel.onopen = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] maximumMessageSize = peerConnection.sctp.maxMessageSize;
  \f[B]const\f[R] textToSend = \(dqThis is my possibly overly long string!\(dq;
  splitStringToMax(textToSend, maximumMessageSize).forEach((elem) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    channel.send(elem);
  });
};
